1
00:01:01,458 --> 00:01:03,542
EPISODE 11

2
00:01:03,543 --> 00:01:06,086
- You're getting off work late, huh?
- I have a shoot tomorrow.

3
00:01:06,087 --> 00:01:07,756
So I wanted to get ready.

4
00:01:13,970 --> 00:01:15,679
- Um, ma'am.
- What?

5
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:17,139
When do you have a moment?

6
00:01:17,140 --> 00:01:18,390
Why do you ask?

7
00:01:18,391 --> 00:01:20,267
It might be a good time
for some new headshots.

8
00:01:20,268 --> 00:01:22,520
You've been getting
a lot of media coverage lately.

9
00:01:22,521 --> 00:01:24,856
We could talk about that later. Not now.

10
00:01:31,863 --> 00:01:33,989
- [alarm blaring]
- [device buzzes]

11
00:01:33,990 --> 00:01:35,826
[Seol-ah] The exit code is different.

12
00:01:49,297 --> 00:01:50,798
[beeping]

13
00:01:50,799 --> 00:01:52,342
[buzzes]

14
00:01:55,303 --> 00:01:56,346
[buzzes]

15
00:01:59,057 --> 00:02:00,475
[door unlocks]

16
00:02:06,273 --> 00:02:08,108
[breathes heavily]

17
00:02:09,985 --> 00:02:11,695
Seol-ah. Seol-ah!

18
00:02:13,321 --> 00:02:14,364
We have to go.

19
00:04:01,721 --> 00:04:04,933
Oh, yes. This is where it belongs.

20
00:04:16,736 --> 00:04:18,071
- Let's go.
- Okay.

21
00:04:24,619 --> 00:04:27,455
[line ringing]

22
00:04:28,581 --> 00:04:31,001
Hey, when will you be wrapping up?

23
00:04:32,002 --> 00:04:33,420
Well, you better hurry up.

24
00:04:34,212 --> 00:04:37,632
We have to finish
before the police end up finding them.

25
00:04:38,425 --> 00:04:39,426
Are you okay?

26
00:04:41,511 --> 00:04:45,056
The things you were looking for,
were they in there?

27
00:04:46,433 --> 00:04:47,642
Yes, they are.

28
00:04:48,309 --> 00:04:51,646
Taemyung's art, the ones
Chair Kim swapped out,

29
00:04:53,023 --> 00:04:54,649
and my dad's painting too.

30
00:04:57,277 --> 00:05:00,696
Everything burned up,
every single photo included.

31
00:05:00,697 --> 00:05:02,657
But my family's last memories

32
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:05,368
are still trapped in there

33
00:05:06,619 --> 00:05:07,870
[sighs]

34
00:05:07,871 --> 00:05:10,790
I will never forgive Chair Kim for this.

35
00:05:12,125 --> 00:05:14,085
I promise I'll make her pay.

36
00:05:15,462 --> 00:05:16,463
I'm with you

37
00:05:17,672 --> 00:05:19,299
whatever you decide.

38
00:05:42,113 --> 00:05:43,239
Have a good time.

39
00:06:00,465 --> 00:06:02,467
[attendees chattering]

40
00:06:08,431 --> 00:06:10,016
Everything's ready, right?

41
00:06:12,685 --> 00:06:15,522
[chattering continues]

42
00:06:41,464 --> 00:06:42,924
SEARCH AND SEIZURE WARRANT
ARREST WARRANT

43
00:06:58,189 --> 00:07:00,107
"Untitled" by Lee Soo-dam.

44
00:07:00,108 --> 00:07:03,026
Sold to a bidder in the room for $270,000.

45
00:07:03,027 --> 00:07:04,737
Congratulations.

46
00:07:14,747 --> 00:07:18,625
This unpublished major work
believed to be the last painting

47
00:07:18,626 --> 00:07:21,587
completed by the late artist Song Hwan-ju,

48
00:07:21,588 --> 00:07:24,381
estimated at over $4.6 million

49
00:07:24,382 --> 00:07:27,927
is expected to surpass
their most famous work, Cheong-myeong.

50
00:07:33,183 --> 00:07:38,437
However, today this artwork
will not be going up for auction.

51
00:07:38,438 --> 00:07:40,356
[audience murmuring]

52
00:07:43,109 --> 00:07:45,153
Because it's not an authentic piece!

53
00:07:49,449 --> 00:07:52,993
This piece was consigned
through unofficial channels...

54
00:07:52,994 --> 00:07:54,244
What's she saying?

55
00:07:54,245 --> 00:07:56,122
...at the direction
of Royal Auction Chair Kim Sun-ae.

56
00:07:56,831 --> 00:08:00,792
The piece was submitted for appraisal,
since I questioned its authenticity,

57
00:08:00,793 --> 00:08:02,628
- and the analysis revealed...
- What is she doing?

58
00:08:02,629 --> 00:08:03,712
- ...that the adhesive used...
- Hey.

59
00:08:03,713 --> 00:08:06,673
- What the hell are you doing, Ms. Han?
- ...was an industrial synthetic resin

60
00:08:06,674 --> 00:08:10,469
rather than the natural glue that
artist Song Hwan-ju insisted on using.

61
00:08:10,470 --> 00:08:12,221
ART AUTHENTICATION REPORT: FORGERY

62
00:08:12,222 --> 00:08:13,473
[sirens blaring]

63
00:08:23,107 --> 00:08:25,025
[Seol-ah] Even the signature is different.

64
00:08:25,026 --> 00:08:26,735
SIGNATURE COMPARISON ANALYSIS
FORGERY - GENUINE

65
00:08:26,736 --> 00:08:28,570
The character for "Hwan" in his name

66
00:08:28,571 --> 00:08:30,530
is written incorrectly,
using the "child" radical

67
00:08:30,531 --> 00:08:32,407
instead of the correct "fire" radical.

68
00:08:32,408 --> 00:08:33,742
[in Spanish] You idiot!

69
00:08:33,743 --> 00:08:36,954
[Seol-ah, in English] Therefore,
the appraisal agency has determined

70
00:08:36,955 --> 00:08:40,499
that this piece is clearly
a forged artwork.

71
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,125
Get her. Drag her down. Okay?

72
00:08:42,126 --> 00:08:43,962
Yes, ma'am. That crazy little...

73
00:08:54,514 --> 00:08:56,014
We have evidence that the works

74
00:08:56,015 --> 00:09:00,936
the Taemyung Cultural Foundation recently
lost in the fire were also forgeries.

75
00:09:00,937 --> 00:09:03,355
Hey! Drag her out!

76
00:09:03,356 --> 00:09:05,941
[Mr. Song] Shit. No photos. No photos!

77
00:09:05,942 --> 00:09:08,778
[Seol-ah] So, where is the real one then?

78
00:09:12,657 --> 00:09:14,074
[audience gasps]

79
00:09:14,075 --> 00:09:16,702
- No way.
- There's the real one.

80
00:09:16,703 --> 00:09:20,205
[Seol-ah] As you can see, she moved them
to her secret storage vault.

81
00:09:20,206 --> 00:09:22,666
Inside is her collection,

82
00:09:22,667 --> 00:09:27,754
all of which was gathered
through embezzlement, theft, and swapping.

83
00:09:27,755 --> 00:09:29,881
[screams]

84
00:09:29,882 --> 00:09:31,508
[reporter 1] How did you get this footage?

85
00:09:31,509 --> 00:09:34,052
[reporter 2] When did you start planning
to blow the whistle on her?

86
00:09:34,053 --> 00:09:35,137
Ma'am!

87
00:09:35,138 --> 00:09:38,141
Is there more evidence that
this was Chair Kim Sun-ae's doing?

88
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:44,313
Artist Han Jin-woo, who painted this work,

89
00:09:44,314 --> 00:09:46,732
was once celebrated
as a genius in the art world,

90
00:09:46,733 --> 00:09:49,986
then was reduced to a mere forger
by Chair Kim.

91
00:09:52,030 --> 00:09:54,824
I'd like to take this opportunity

92
00:09:55,783 --> 00:09:59,704
to restore the honor of the artist
who died under a cloud of disgrace.

93
00:10:00,330 --> 00:10:04,249
Even at this very moment,
another forgery orchestrated by Chair Kim

94
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:06,252
is likely being created somewhere.

95
00:10:07,045 --> 00:10:10,422
I therefore request that
the police investigate this thoroughly.

96
00:10:10,423 --> 00:10:12,842
[dramatic music plays]

97
00:10:19,140 --> 00:10:24,102
Hey, do you think people would actually
believe that doctored footage?

98
00:10:24,103 --> 00:10:25,855
- [door opens]
- [people gasping]

99
00:10:29,567 --> 00:10:30,818
Ms. Kim Sun-ae.

100
00:10:31,486 --> 00:10:33,653
You're under arrest
for embezzlement and fraud,

101
00:10:33,654 --> 00:10:36,282
and for violating
the Criminal Proceeds Act.

102
00:10:37,867 --> 00:10:39,826
At least the police seem to believe it.

103
00:10:39,827 --> 00:10:41,495
- Ma'am, ma'am...
- Let go.

104
00:10:41,496 --> 00:10:45,500
I did nothing wrong. How dare you...
You guys are making a mistake!

105
00:11:01,891 --> 00:11:02,891
[sighs]

106
00:11:02,892 --> 00:11:03,976
What is all this?

107
00:11:04,477 --> 00:11:06,813
[Eun-gyeom] Wow, is this supposed
to be an art gallery?

108
00:11:07,605 --> 00:11:09,107
How much money did she pocket this way?

109
00:11:18,699 --> 00:11:21,034
[Gong] We've secured
all the evidence from your office.

110
00:11:21,035 --> 00:11:22,202
What?

111
00:11:22,203 --> 00:11:25,998
Who do you people think you are,
going into my office, huh?

112
00:11:26,624 --> 00:11:30,128
Don't touch anything!
Don't touch anything! It's all mine!

113
00:11:30,962 --> 00:11:33,672
Don't touch anything!
Do not touch anything.

114
00:11:33,673 --> 00:11:35,799
- They're all mine! Don't touch anything.
- Come on!

115
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:37,510
Hey, Han Seol-ah!

116
00:11:38,094 --> 00:11:41,013
Hey! Han Seol-ah!

117
00:11:44,892 --> 00:11:45,977
Let go!

118
00:11:47,061 --> 00:11:48,354
Han Seol-ah!

119
00:12:13,504 --> 00:12:16,507
They'll install locking devices
and restrict access.

120
00:12:17,175 --> 00:12:19,135
Since there are so many high-value works,

121
00:12:19,927 --> 00:12:23,639
the vault will be sealed until they can
be moved to a separate location.

122
00:12:24,807 --> 00:12:27,727
We need to cross-check the evidence that
you submitted.

123
00:12:28,352 --> 00:12:32,231
Could you verify them
before the expert appraisal?

124
00:12:34,901 --> 00:12:37,444
You won't find this painting on the list.

125
00:12:37,445 --> 00:12:41,157
The original artist is Han Jin-woo.
He was my father.

126
00:12:44,285 --> 00:12:45,828
It can be returned, right?

127
00:12:46,829 --> 00:12:49,874
- Make sure Seol-ah can get it back.
- Okay.

128
00:13:00,593 --> 00:13:01,718
[Woo-seok] What is this?

129
00:13:01,719 --> 00:13:03,304
It hasn't been unwrapped yet.

130
00:13:07,266 --> 00:13:08,267
[gasps]

131
00:13:12,522 --> 00:13:13,523
The Stiller.

132
00:13:14,690 --> 00:13:16,567
The painting worth over $10 million?

133
00:13:18,611 --> 00:13:20,446
No way. She swapped this one too?

134
00:13:21,239 --> 00:13:23,950
It's the authentic Stiller piece
from the exhibition hall.

135
00:13:25,201 --> 00:13:28,246
Does that mean
she's making a forgery of this too?

136
00:13:29,163 --> 00:13:30,623
[tense music plays]

137
00:13:41,384 --> 00:13:42,843
- Woo-seok, wait.
- I'll call you.

138
00:14:04,907 --> 00:14:06,700
[line ringing]

139
00:14:06,701 --> 00:14:08,411
You're still at the auction house?

140
00:14:08,911 --> 00:14:10,037
Do you have a minute?

141
00:14:12,456 --> 00:14:14,249
Get everyone to leave the worksite.

142
00:14:14,250 --> 00:14:16,669
[sighs] I'll do the cleanup.
Just leave now!

143
00:14:17,503 --> 00:14:19,505
Do as I say, you idiots!

144
00:14:20,590 --> 00:14:21,591
Shit.

145
00:15:31,661 --> 00:15:33,329
[door opens]

146
00:15:34,205 --> 00:15:35,622
The hell?

147
00:15:35,623 --> 00:15:37,541
You guys still haven't left?

148
00:15:44,465 --> 00:15:45,591
Who's there?

149
00:15:58,521 --> 00:16:01,523
It's been a while, Ju Hyun-su.

150
00:16:01,524 --> 00:16:03,192
[sighs] Shit...

151
00:16:04,026 --> 00:16:06,277
You were the investigator
in the Taemyung case?

152
00:16:06,278 --> 00:16:08,405
You can't run anymore, you bastard.

153
00:16:08,406 --> 00:16:10,657
Get ready to rot in prison.

154
00:16:10,658 --> 00:16:13,327
I can just burn everything
and I'll be fine.

155
00:16:14,787 --> 00:16:16,497
Do you want to die too, you bastard?

156
00:16:20,334 --> 00:16:21,668
Goddamn it...

157
00:16:21,669 --> 00:16:23,545
You just confessed, didn't you?

158
00:16:23,546 --> 00:16:25,463
- Shit...
- That you killed Woo-hee!

159
00:16:25,464 --> 00:16:28,091
My life got screwed up
after meeting that bitch!

160
00:16:28,092 --> 00:16:30,552
If I knew her brother was a cop,
I wouldn't have touched her.

161
00:16:30,553 --> 00:16:32,595
Shut your mouth, you bastard!

162
00:16:32,596 --> 00:16:35,181
[laughs] She was crazy about me.

163
00:16:35,182 --> 00:16:37,517
She begged me to take her in that truck.

164
00:16:37,518 --> 00:16:40,562
That girl was so starved for affection.

165
00:16:40,563 --> 00:16:43,231
- [laughs]
- I said shut up, you son of a bitch!

166
00:16:43,232 --> 00:16:44,817
[Woo-seok screams]

167
00:16:47,570 --> 00:16:49,196
[grunts]

168
00:16:52,116 --> 00:16:54,160
[shouting]

169
00:16:56,704 --> 00:16:58,621
[breathes heavily]

170
00:16:58,622 --> 00:16:59,707
Come here.

171
00:17:07,631 --> 00:17:10,759
She was so young
but she didn't want to be a burden

172
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:13,846
to her big brother. Did you know that?

173
00:17:14,972 --> 00:17:17,850
That bitch's death, it's all your fault.

174
00:17:18,434 --> 00:17:19,851
No.

175
00:17:19,852 --> 00:17:22,812
No! No! No!

176
00:17:22,813 --> 00:17:25,690
No. You son of a bitch!

177
00:17:25,691 --> 00:17:27,442
- Die, you bastard!
- [Seol-ah] Hey, grab him!

178
00:17:27,443 --> 00:17:28,735
- [Gong] Woo-seok, stop!
- Die!

179
00:17:28,736 --> 00:17:30,320
[Woo-seok shouting]

180
00:17:30,321 --> 00:17:32,113
- Stop!
- [Gong] Stop! Stop it.

181
00:17:32,114 --> 00:17:35,784
- Woo-seok, stop. Stop, that's enough.
- [Gong] Hey!

182
00:17:35,785 --> 00:17:37,328
Please.

183
00:17:40,539 --> 00:17:42,291
- Hey.
- [grunts]

184
00:17:48,422 --> 00:17:49,507
[Gong] Come on!

185
00:18:05,481 --> 00:18:06,482
[breathing heavily]

186
00:18:18,035 --> 00:18:19,411
Hey, it's all over now.

187
00:18:21,080 --> 00:18:22,456
You can relax.

188
00:18:25,084 --> 00:18:27,127
[sobbing]

189
00:18:28,838 --> 00:18:30,922
[gentle music plays]

190
00:18:30,923 --> 00:18:32,174
It was me...

191
00:18:34,385 --> 00:18:36,846
I'm the one who made Woo-hee like that.

192
00:18:38,013 --> 00:18:39,181
It was me.

193
00:18:40,099 --> 00:18:41,851
[sobbing continues]

194
00:18:43,143 --> 00:18:44,770
You said the same thing to me too,

195
00:18:46,230 --> 00:18:48,022
that it wasn't my fault.

196
00:18:48,023 --> 00:18:51,193
And now, I'll return those words to you.

197
00:18:52,486 --> 00:18:54,196
It's not your fault, Woo-seok.

198
00:18:54,947 --> 00:18:56,407
You always did your best.

199
00:18:57,116 --> 00:18:58,784
Let me say that back to you.

200
00:19:24,184 --> 00:19:25,477
[Gong] Ah, geez.

201
00:19:27,730 --> 00:19:28,981
[sighs]

202
00:19:43,495 --> 00:19:45,372
[Woo-hee] Please don't get hurt.

203
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:51,086
You know you're all I have, brother.

204
00:20:03,974 --> 00:20:05,225
[chuckles]

205
00:20:06,852 --> 00:20:07,978
[chuckles]

206
00:20:16,654 --> 00:20:19,448
[Hyun-su] That bitch's death.
It's all your fault.

207
00:20:28,540 --> 00:20:29,541
[sighs]

208
00:20:34,505 --> 00:20:36,756
[Gong] Your name. I know it's Ju Hyun-su.

209
00:20:36,757 --> 00:20:37,925
STATEMENT

210
00:20:38,509 --> 00:20:39,510
Your date of birth.

211
00:20:43,472 --> 00:20:46,975
Hey. Think you can pull
that right to remain silent crap? Geez.

212
00:20:46,976 --> 00:20:48,268
[sighs]

213
00:20:51,897 --> 00:20:55,650
- What the hell...
- This is the file on the Cha Woo-hee case.

214
00:20:55,651 --> 00:20:58,779
I couldn't throw it away
for six whole years.

215
00:20:59,697 --> 00:21:01,615
When Woo-seok was
practically spitting blood,

216
00:21:02,241 --> 00:21:03,534
saying you killed his sister,

217
00:21:04,118 --> 00:21:06,704
I laughed in his face.
I told him he was just being emotional.

218
00:21:07,454 --> 00:21:10,958
You already killed someone once,
so you expect us to believe you now?

219
00:21:12,251 --> 00:21:14,002
Start talking, you bastard!

220
00:21:14,003 --> 00:21:16,754
How far did Chair Kim go?
You killed Paek Jun-beom, right?

221
00:21:16,755 --> 00:21:19,049
No! I didn't kill Paek Jun-beom!

222
00:21:20,342 --> 00:21:21,510
Then who did you kill?

223
00:21:22,803 --> 00:21:24,138
Did you kill Cha Woo-hee?

224
00:21:26,473 --> 00:21:28,267
Did you kill Kim Yun-ji?

225
00:21:29,059 --> 00:21:31,520
[sighs] Shit...

226
00:21:46,035 --> 00:21:47,453
What is all this?

227
00:21:48,454 --> 00:21:49,996
I wanted to prepare you something.

228
00:21:49,997 --> 00:21:51,956
Oh, no. I'm fine. Thanks.

229
00:21:51,957 --> 00:21:54,792
I-I mean, it must be hard for you
to use fire.

230
00:21:54,793 --> 00:21:57,087
It's an induction stove,
I think I can handle it.

231
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:59,798
[exhales heavily] But you don't have to.

232
00:22:00,716 --> 00:22:02,384
- Uh... Should I wash this first?
- Uh...

233
00:22:04,344 --> 00:22:08,223
Go inside and get some rest.
You've already been through a lot.

234
00:22:16,023 --> 00:22:18,942
You know, I'm not very good at cooking.

235
00:22:20,319 --> 00:22:23,322
Especially when someone is watching me.

236
00:22:30,746 --> 00:22:31,747
[chuckles]

237
00:22:40,631 --> 00:22:41,840
CARROT

238
00:22:43,842 --> 00:22:44,968
GREEN ONION

239
00:22:57,022 --> 00:22:58,440
ADD THE BEEF

240
00:23:21,296 --> 00:23:22,881
I can't promise it'll taste good.

241
00:23:25,592 --> 00:23:27,636
This was my first time making porridge.

242
00:23:32,141 --> 00:23:35,561
I just thought it'd be easier to eat
than plain rice.

243
00:23:38,772 --> 00:23:39,773
Thank you.

244
00:23:42,609 --> 00:23:43,652
It looks great.

245
00:24:04,965 --> 00:24:06,216
Delicious.

246
00:24:14,141 --> 00:24:18,770
I often thought about the meal
you made for me.

247
00:24:19,563 --> 00:24:21,272
After the police interrogation,

248
00:24:21,273 --> 00:24:24,109
when I broke physically and mentally.

249
00:24:25,527 --> 00:24:30,574
That warm bowl of rice you made
helped me get back on my feet again.

250
00:24:33,952 --> 00:24:35,871
But you didn't wanna see me anymore.

251
00:24:36,872 --> 00:24:38,207
I was afraid...

252
00:24:41,001 --> 00:24:45,464
that something might happen to you
if you stayed by my side.

253
00:24:48,926 --> 00:24:50,344
And how about now?

254
00:24:52,554 --> 00:24:54,306
I'm still scared, even now.

255
00:24:56,266 --> 00:24:59,102
But I... I will give it a try.

256
00:25:00,687 --> 00:25:02,397
You are the one who taught me that.

257
00:25:03,065 --> 00:25:06,860
You told me not to run away
or to push you away,

258
00:25:08,445 --> 00:25:10,822
to stay by your side and keep you safe.

259
00:25:13,784 --> 00:25:17,746
I think now I understand
about how you're feeling.

260
00:25:20,999 --> 00:25:22,000
But

261
00:25:23,252 --> 00:25:24,836
we have to keep going.

262
00:25:27,714 --> 00:25:30,008
I cant promise that
things will get better,

263
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:32,761
because

264
00:25:34,179 --> 00:25:36,807
we'll carry this pain
for the rest of our lives.

265
00:25:40,143 --> 00:25:42,271
Let's get through it together.

266
00:25:44,898 --> 00:25:45,983
[gulps]

267
00:25:55,242 --> 00:25:56,243
Hurry up and eat.

268
00:25:58,287 --> 00:25:59,413
It's really good.

269
00:26:01,373 --> 00:26:02,416
[chuckles]

270
00:26:09,548 --> 00:26:10,924
[sniffles]

271
00:26:28,859 --> 00:26:31,152
We analyzed Chair Kim's computer

272
00:26:31,153 --> 00:26:34,281
and found chats with Kim Yun-ji
on the company messenger.

273
00:26:34,865 --> 00:26:36,365
I think you should take a look at them.

274
00:26:36,366 --> 00:26:37,617
ASSOCIATE AUCTIONEER KIM YUN-JI

275
00:26:38,285 --> 00:26:39,827
[Ms. Kim] The painting my father bought,

276
00:26:39,828 --> 00:26:42,621
you personally brought it in
from New York, right?

277
00:26:42,622 --> 00:26:44,206
[Chair Kim] Why do you ask?

278
00:26:44,207 --> 00:26:46,125
[Ms. Kim] Isn't this
completely crossing the line?

279
00:26:46,126 --> 00:26:48,962
I introduced that painting to my family
in good faith.

280
00:26:49,755 --> 00:26:52,341
[Chair Kim] Come up. Let's talk in person.

281
00:26:54,760 --> 00:26:55,968
[Ms. Kim] Funny, isn't it?

282
00:26:55,969 --> 00:27:00,222
The head of the Tax Investigation Bureau
has a daughter who's an auctioneer,

283
00:27:00,223 --> 00:27:02,266
yet there's a forgery in his house.

284
00:27:02,267 --> 00:27:04,811
What kind of nonsense are you saying?

285
00:27:05,437 --> 00:27:08,774
I had two outside appraisals done,
and the results are the same.

286
00:27:09,399 --> 00:27:13,528
If my dad finds out,
what do you think will happen?

287
00:27:14,112 --> 00:27:16,031
Are you threatening me right now?

288
00:27:16,907 --> 00:27:19,326
I'm saying we should try to sort this out.

289
00:27:19,826 --> 00:27:20,994
What is it you want?

290
00:27:22,412 --> 00:27:23,580
The main auction podium.

291
00:27:24,247 --> 00:27:25,415
[scoffs]

292
00:27:27,250 --> 00:27:29,252
You want me to get rid of Ms. Han?

293
00:27:30,462 --> 00:27:33,298
This must've put
a lot of pressure on Chair Kim.

294
00:27:33,799 --> 00:27:35,966
She already had plenty to worry about.

295
00:27:35,967 --> 00:27:38,553
I thought it could be a motive
for Kim Yun-ji's murder.

296
00:27:45,894 --> 00:27:48,646
[Seong-il] Taemyung's paintings
that supposedly burned in the fire

297
00:27:48,647 --> 00:27:51,108
were found in your secret vault,
and you know nothing about it?

298
00:27:52,567 --> 00:27:56,320
My client was simply storing the paintings
at the customer's request.

299
00:27:56,321 --> 00:28:00,366
This is a matter of Taemyung's negligence
and an insurance issue,

300
00:28:00,367 --> 00:28:02,494
not a crime committed by my client.

301
00:28:04,413 --> 00:28:05,997
Then let's talk about this.

302
00:28:06,623 --> 00:28:09,251
That Stiller painting
worth over six million dollars.

303
00:28:09,751 --> 00:28:12,504
You just happened to swoop in
when the owner died, didn't you?

304
00:28:13,463 --> 00:28:15,924
[gulps, clears throat] The same goes here.

305
00:28:17,050 --> 00:28:20,469
My client simply kept the artwork
in the vault

306
00:28:20,470 --> 00:28:23,056
until the inheritance process
was finalized.

307
00:28:23,890 --> 00:28:25,516
That's standard practice.

308
00:28:25,517 --> 00:28:28,061
But then why did you make a forgery?

309
00:28:30,063 --> 00:28:31,440
Why all that trouble?

310
00:28:32,858 --> 00:28:36,278
Your lackey, Ju Hyun-su, has been caught.

311
00:28:37,070 --> 00:28:39,405
[moody music plays]

312
00:28:39,406 --> 00:28:43,451
There is no point in keeping this up,
Ms. Kim Sun-ae.

313
00:28:43,452 --> 00:28:44,536
[sighs]

314
00:28:45,370 --> 00:28:47,038
The way you speak

315
00:28:47,747 --> 00:28:49,374
is very rude.

316
00:28:50,167 --> 00:28:54,671
Mr. Detective, do you even have an idea
of who I am?

317
00:28:55,922 --> 00:29:00,135
Well, the mistake's already been made
and can't be undone.

318
00:29:00,802 --> 00:29:06,349
Whether your career as a cop goes down
a flower path or a thorny one

319
00:29:06,892 --> 00:29:08,935
depends on this moment.

320
00:29:09,769 --> 00:29:11,145
Can't you feel that?

321
00:29:11,146 --> 00:29:12,981
You should be worrying about yourself.

322
00:29:13,899 --> 00:29:17,610
Insurance fraud, embezzlement,
selling forgeries,

323
00:29:17,611 --> 00:29:21,114
and even incitement to murder.

324
00:29:27,078 --> 00:29:29,289
You have a lot of nerve, you know?

325
00:29:30,207 --> 00:29:34,002
How ungrateful can you be
to stab Chair Kim in the back?

326
00:29:35,420 --> 00:29:37,379
What exactly are you really after?

327
00:29:37,380 --> 00:29:39,925
Are you trying to become CEO
while she's away?

328
00:29:40,675 --> 00:29:42,677
That's probably what you are after.

329
00:29:43,386 --> 00:29:45,596
Who do you think
you're slandering right now?

330
00:29:45,597 --> 00:29:46,681
Hey.

331
00:29:47,390 --> 00:29:48,517
You think I'm you?

332
00:29:49,768 --> 00:29:53,772
I'm just doing what I can
to sort things out from my position.

333
00:29:54,523 --> 00:29:57,567
I should own what I started.

334
00:30:00,237 --> 00:30:01,238
[scoffs]

335
00:30:01,905 --> 00:30:02,906
Fine.

336
00:30:03,406 --> 00:30:05,742
I don't know how long it'll last,
but good luck.

337
00:30:06,368 --> 00:30:07,994
Chair Kim will be out soon.

338
00:30:09,538 --> 00:30:10,580
[Tae-seok sighs]

339
00:30:11,706 --> 00:30:13,999
Our upcoming auctions will probably
fall through, won't they?

340
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:16,419
We've already had
this many client complaints.

341
00:30:17,003 --> 00:30:18,629
Most are canceling consignments.

342
00:30:18,630 --> 00:30:20,506
[grunts] So annoying.

343
00:30:20,507 --> 00:30:23,175
[Seol-ah] Give me the list.
I'll call them myself

344
00:30:23,176 --> 00:30:24,927
and try to convince them to stay.

345
00:30:24,928 --> 00:30:28,013
Ms. Han, you came to work?

346
00:30:28,014 --> 00:30:29,391
Are you all right?

347
00:30:30,016 --> 00:30:32,017
I owe you all an apology.

348
00:30:32,018 --> 00:30:36,188
I know better than anyone
how much you all love Royal Auction,

349
00:30:36,189 --> 00:30:37,690
yet I caused all of this.

350
00:30:37,691 --> 00:30:40,068
That's why I'm really sorry.

351
00:30:40,902 --> 00:30:43,071
Gosh, no. You did the right thing.

352
00:30:44,990 --> 00:30:47,576
Honestly, we all think it's for the best.

353
00:30:48,118 --> 00:30:51,120
We were unknowingly participating
in Chair Kim's fraud,

354
00:30:51,121 --> 00:30:52,581
so it's actually a relief.

355
00:30:56,668 --> 00:30:58,335
Ma'am remember you put your trust in us...

356
00:30:58,336 --> 00:31:00,379
[client 1] They talked about
forgeries and embezzlement,

357
00:31:00,380 --> 00:31:01,463
how can I believe you?

358
00:31:01,464 --> 00:31:03,299
So we will take full responsibility
for every--

359
00:31:03,300 --> 00:31:06,010
Do you think I'd be okay with it?
Send my paintings back right now!

360
00:31:06,011 --> 00:31:07,469
I promise that I will visit you--

361
00:31:07,470 --> 00:31:10,472
I don't care about compensation.
I'm done doing business with you!

362
00:31:10,473 --> 00:31:11,558
[line clicks]

363
00:31:20,191 --> 00:31:22,360
- [knocks on door]
- [door opens]

364
00:31:24,237 --> 00:31:25,989
Um, Ms. Han.

365
00:31:26,823 --> 00:31:31,077
Artist Han Jin-woo, he's your, uh,
family, isn't he?

366
00:31:32,954 --> 00:31:35,457
Mm-hmm. He's my father.

367
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:40,003
I had no idea you were going
through so much pain.

368
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:44,007
I'm sorry that I couldn't be there
for you more.

369
00:31:44,591 --> 00:31:45,841
Thank you.

370
00:31:45,842 --> 00:31:48,427
I really appreciate the warm welcome.

371
00:31:48,428 --> 00:31:50,013
I thought I'd be chewed out.

372
00:31:50,639 --> 00:31:53,975
It must've been so hard for you.

373
00:31:55,101 --> 00:31:57,519
Things will get harder for all of us.

374
00:31:57,520 --> 00:32:01,316
I'll do anything.
I'm ready for what's coming.

375
00:32:12,619 --> 00:32:17,457
I thought only Cha Woo-seok was sincere,
but Han Seol-ah is sincere too.

376
00:32:18,750 --> 00:32:21,502
[sighs] Yeesh, it makes my head spin.

377
00:32:21,503 --> 00:32:24,421
I can't imagine
what would have happened to you...

378
00:32:24,422 --> 00:32:27,717
I had to make him pay for what he did.

379
00:32:29,094 --> 00:32:31,387
Captain's even angrier than I am.

380
00:32:31,388 --> 00:32:33,514
I think he feels so guilty towards you.

381
00:32:33,515 --> 00:32:35,016
[sighs]

382
00:32:35,725 --> 00:32:38,269
Have that bastard and Chair Kim
confessed yet?

383
00:32:38,853 --> 00:32:40,270
We will make them.

384
00:32:40,271 --> 00:32:44,400
Do you actually think Chair Kim
killed someone over a painting?

385
00:32:44,401 --> 00:32:46,944
So far, she's the suspect
with the clearest motive.

386
00:32:46,945 --> 00:32:48,779
Even if she didn't do it herself,

387
00:32:48,780 --> 00:32:50,781
she could have ordered Ju Hyun-su.

388
00:32:50,782 --> 00:32:52,783
He was out of the country for a long time.

389
00:32:52,784 --> 00:32:55,704
And why would Chair Kim
mess with Han Seol-ah's men?

390
00:32:57,789 --> 00:33:01,500
You know, I still suspect Do Eun-hyuk,
but he has an alibi.

391
00:33:01,501 --> 00:33:03,586
[tense music playing]

392
00:33:05,088 --> 00:33:09,508
The CCTV footage shows that he was
at his studio in Cheongun

393
00:33:09,509 --> 00:33:11,260
when Paek Jun-beom was killed.

394
00:33:11,261 --> 00:33:12,636
Let me see that.

395
00:33:12,637 --> 00:33:14,722
You know I can't show you official files.

396
00:33:14,723 --> 00:33:17,224
Well, there were records seized
from Paek Jun-beom's house,

397
00:33:17,225 --> 00:33:19,184
of him stalking Han Seol-ah, right?

398
00:33:19,185 --> 00:33:20,854
Including the photos taken in Cheongun.

399
00:33:21,646 --> 00:33:22,647
[sighs]

400
00:33:24,774 --> 00:33:26,024
Could you, please?

401
00:33:26,025 --> 00:33:27,110
[sighs]

402
00:33:29,237 --> 00:33:31,239
[ominous music plays]

403
00:33:43,501 --> 00:33:47,588
[Gong] The cell tower data shows that
Do Eun-hyuk was at his Cheongun studio

404
00:33:47,589 --> 00:33:49,549
when Paek Jun-beom was killed.

405
00:33:52,969 --> 00:33:56,973
Now, I understand why
you trusted Cha Woo-seok.

406
00:33:59,142 --> 00:34:03,813
I never imagined someone
like Chair Kim could actually be arrested,

407
00:34:04,773 --> 00:34:08,359
and that's not something
I could've helped with.

408
00:34:09,402 --> 00:34:12,071
I figured that's why you joined
sides with Cha Woo-seok.

409
00:34:12,906 --> 00:34:14,073
No, not really.

410
00:34:14,741 --> 00:34:17,994
We both had things we had to do,
and somewhere along the way,

411
00:34:18,703 --> 00:34:20,789
we ended up having the same purpose,

412
00:34:22,499 --> 00:34:23,917
so we worked together.

413
00:34:26,836 --> 00:34:30,673
So it's a special connection.
Could it be fate?

414
00:34:32,342 --> 00:34:33,676
Tell me what do you think?

415
00:34:35,887 --> 00:34:37,388
You have a good eye for people.

416
00:34:38,890 --> 00:34:40,683
[gentle music playing]

417
00:34:44,521 --> 00:34:46,648
[gulps, sighs]

418
00:34:47,357 --> 00:34:49,526
He's a person who belongs
in the spotlight,

419
00:34:51,444 --> 00:34:53,363
confident and straightforward.

420
00:34:54,280 --> 00:34:55,448
I'm the opposite.

421
00:34:57,367 --> 00:34:59,536
Because I belong in the background.

422
00:35:02,914 --> 00:35:06,751
You see, I've been deliberately
ignoring this...

423
00:35:08,795 --> 00:35:10,630
but now I see it clearly.

424
00:35:12,257 --> 00:35:14,133
Why would you think that?

425
00:35:15,093 --> 00:35:17,262
[sighs] People...

426
00:35:19,305 --> 00:35:21,724
live according to what's ingrained
in them.

427
00:35:25,645 --> 00:35:27,897
Anyway, you've done a lot to get this far.

428
00:35:28,481 --> 00:35:29,566
Everything will be fine.

429
00:35:30,358 --> 00:35:33,194
I hope you get
Mr. Han's painting back too.

430
00:35:33,945 --> 00:35:35,737
I'm still on edge.

431
00:35:35,738 --> 00:35:39,284
You know, Chair Kim isn't the type
to go down quietly.

432
00:35:41,578 --> 00:35:42,579
Don't worry.

433
00:35:44,455 --> 00:35:46,541
It'll all work out the way you want.

434
00:35:58,970 --> 00:36:00,972
[ominous music plays]

435
00:36:26,956 --> 00:36:28,165
[knocks on door]

436
00:36:28,166 --> 00:36:30,877
Ms. Han, Chair Kim is here.

437
00:36:35,298 --> 00:36:38,718
They think there's no risk of escape,
for health reasons.

438
00:36:39,636 --> 00:36:40,928
It's always the same, you know?

439
00:36:40,929 --> 00:36:43,263
Damn, are these guys for real?

440
00:36:43,264 --> 00:36:45,015
She brought in a big law firm.

441
00:36:45,016 --> 00:36:46,767
Looks like their strategy worked.

442
00:36:46,768 --> 00:36:48,853
[liquid pouring]

443
00:36:52,774 --> 00:36:56,778
- [footsteps approaching]
- [slurps]

444
00:37:10,500 --> 00:37:11,668
Sit down.

445
00:37:20,093 --> 00:37:23,221
What's been going through your head
all this time, huh?

446
00:37:23,972 --> 00:37:27,599
Have you been living
with such determination

447
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:29,560
to avenge your father?

448
00:37:31,104 --> 00:37:33,105
Well, I learned it all from you, ma'am.

449
00:37:33,106 --> 00:37:35,233
[scoffs]

450
00:37:39,153 --> 00:37:42,407
My father was a theater sign painter.

451
00:37:43,116 --> 00:37:45,534
I used to help him with painting,

452
00:37:45,535 --> 00:37:50,081
and then I became an apprentice
to become a real painter.

453
00:37:50,707 --> 00:37:53,584
But while watching your dad there,
I realized...

454
00:37:54,544 --> 00:37:55,712
[sighs]

455
00:37:56,212 --> 00:38:00,383
"Even a genius like him
can starve in this business."

456
00:38:01,884 --> 00:38:04,012
So you made him paint forgeries?

457
00:38:06,681 --> 00:38:11,435
It was to help him make a living,
so your family wouldn't starve to death.

458
00:38:11,436 --> 00:38:14,771
Hey, is it my fault that naive man

459
00:38:14,772 --> 00:38:17,150
took out loans
just so he could pay it all back?

460
00:38:17,734 --> 00:38:21,069
Do you really think that's, uh, an excuse
for causing his death?

461
00:38:21,070 --> 00:38:24,281
Who caused his death?
That was his own choice.

462
00:38:24,282 --> 00:38:28,702
I was the one who called 119
when your house caught fire.

463
00:38:28,703 --> 00:38:30,620
It was me! I saved you!

464
00:38:30,621 --> 00:38:32,999
You should've let me die back then!

465
00:38:35,168 --> 00:38:37,170
I wouldn't have suffered like this.

466
00:38:38,379 --> 00:38:40,798
Because I survived at the cost
of my parents' lives,

467
00:38:41,382 --> 00:38:43,884
I had to wag my tail like a dog
in front of you

468
00:38:43,885 --> 00:38:46,262
and smile until my mouth split.

469
00:38:48,931 --> 00:38:51,808
Even if you get away this time,

470
00:38:51,809 --> 00:38:54,395
I will hunt you down
to the ends of the Earth.

471
00:38:56,522 --> 00:38:57,523
[scoffs]

472
00:38:59,275 --> 00:39:00,777
What more can you do?

473
00:39:01,903 --> 00:39:04,822
The prosecutors and judges
are on my side anyway.

474
00:39:05,990 --> 00:39:09,534
You know, a dog might bite
its owner's hand once,

475
00:39:09,535 --> 00:39:13,790
but after that,
all it gets is beaten to death.

476
00:39:15,917 --> 00:39:18,336
So if I bite your neck,
it'll be the end of it.

477
00:39:19,337 --> 00:39:20,963
[chuckles]

478
00:39:22,048 --> 00:39:24,342
Do you think you'll even get the chance?

479
00:39:25,134 --> 00:39:28,470
Your neck will be the one on the line.

480
00:39:28,471 --> 00:39:30,890
[laughs]

481
00:39:33,476 --> 00:39:37,605
I guess we'll just have to wait and see...

482
00:39:40,233 --> 00:39:42,067
as to whose neck is on the line.

483
00:39:42,068 --> 00:39:44,445
[tense music playing]

484
00:40:08,886 --> 00:40:10,054
[screams]

485
00:40:12,932 --> 00:40:14,350
[breathes heavily]

486
00:40:22,483 --> 00:40:23,693
[line rings]

487
00:40:24,443 --> 00:40:26,361
Ju Hyun-su is getting out soon.

488
00:40:26,362 --> 00:40:28,697
Take care of that bastard quietly.

489
00:40:28,698 --> 00:40:29,782
If you fail,

490
00:40:31,409 --> 00:40:33,910
then that bitch is going
to learn the secret

491
00:40:33,911 --> 00:40:36,831
that you fear more than your own death.

492
00:40:38,541 --> 00:40:39,542
[line clicks]

493
00:41:08,487 --> 00:41:10,364
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

494
00:41:18,998 --> 00:41:21,000
[soft guitar music playing]

495
00:41:29,133 --> 00:41:31,761
[humming]

496
00:41:35,014 --> 00:41:37,016
[singing in Spanish]

497
00:41:51,155 --> 00:41:53,157
[humming]

498
00:42:10,508 --> 00:42:12,510
[singing continues]

499
00:43:02,560 --> 00:43:04,562
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

500
00:43:32,465 --> 00:43:34,467
[mysterious music playing]

501
00:43:51,650 --> 00:43:54,236
[Woo-seok] Something's off.
Everything's too perfect.

502
00:44:05,539 --> 00:44:06,540
[sighs]

503
00:44:17,051 --> 00:44:18,177
Where are you going?

504
00:44:20,513 --> 00:44:21,555
Chair Kim's office.

505
00:44:22,139 --> 00:44:23,182
She called you?

506
00:44:23,933 --> 00:44:24,934
No.

507
00:44:26,519 --> 00:44:28,062
I'm going up to resign.

508
00:44:29,855 --> 00:44:31,941
Until the last auction... [sighs]

509
00:44:32,608 --> 00:44:35,485
...I wanted to take responsibility
for all the mess,

510
00:44:35,486 --> 00:44:38,072
- but Chair Kim...
- She wouldn't leave you alone.

511
00:44:38,656 --> 00:44:41,158
Let's go together. I'm quitting too.

512
00:44:42,034 --> 00:44:44,077
I told you, you didn't have to do that.

513
00:44:44,078 --> 00:44:49,417
I'd like to focus on my own work now.
And to get back in the water.

514
00:44:50,084 --> 00:44:53,087
[elevator dings, door opens]

515
00:45:13,065 --> 00:45:15,067
[record player scratching]

516
00:46:18,005 --> 00:46:20,381
[gasps]

517
00:46:20,382 --> 00:46:23,177
[screaming, gasping]

518
00:47:02,800 --> 00:47:05,928
According to the security guard,
he heard music playing all night long.

519
00:47:06,554 --> 00:47:08,763
Han Seol-ah and Do Eun-hyuk
were the first to find her.

520
00:47:08,764 --> 00:47:10,891
- Any foul play?
- Nothing yet.

521
00:47:11,475 --> 00:47:13,810
There's a suicide note on her laptop,

522
00:47:13,811 --> 00:47:16,354
but that's not enough
to conclude it was suicide.

523
00:47:16,355 --> 00:47:19,148
The CCTV around her office isn't working.

524
00:47:19,149 --> 00:47:20,567
[scoffs]

525
00:47:20,568 --> 00:47:23,611
She had to move the paintings
to her vault in secret.

526
00:47:23,612 --> 00:47:27,533
[sighs] In the end,
even her death became a secret.

527
00:47:33,914 --> 00:47:35,248
HAN SEOL-AH

528
00:47:35,249 --> 00:47:38,502
[voicemail] The phone you are trying
to reach is turned off. You'll be direct--

529
00:47:39,086 --> 00:47:41,088
[tires squealing]

530
00:48:27,217 --> 00:48:29,219
[doorbell rings]

531
00:48:46,654 --> 00:48:47,696
[sighs]

532
00:48:58,916 --> 00:49:01,710
This isn't the ending
that I was hoping for.

533
00:49:02,920 --> 00:49:05,546
Chair Kim would never kill herself.

534
00:49:05,547 --> 00:49:07,548
When I met her the day before,

535
00:49:07,549 --> 00:49:11,220
she still showed no guilt
and was completely confident.

536
00:49:12,513 --> 00:49:15,474
It looked like someone
had gone through her office.

537
00:49:17,810 --> 00:49:20,937
It's strange that
she wrote the suicide note on her laptop.

538
00:49:20,938 --> 00:49:24,400
She's the kind of person who still
keeps her ledgers written by hand.

539
00:49:28,654 --> 00:49:30,197
That means Chair Kim was also...

540
00:49:31,782 --> 00:49:33,200
It's all connected.

541
00:49:34,868 --> 00:49:36,495
For some reason,

542
00:49:37,121 --> 00:49:38,997
I think it's the work of one person.

543
00:49:39,873 --> 00:49:41,625
So until we catch the killer,

544
00:49:42,209 --> 00:49:43,752
nothing is over yet.

545
00:49:47,464 --> 00:49:48,465
[Woo-seok sighs]

546
00:49:52,136 --> 00:49:53,721
[Woo-seok gasps] Seol-ah.

547
00:49:54,847 --> 00:49:55,889
Are you okay?

548
00:49:57,349 --> 00:49:59,184
Wait, that's dangerous. I got it. Hold on.

549
00:50:26,253 --> 00:50:27,296
[Seung-jae] Seol-ah,

550
00:50:28,464 --> 00:50:31,675
I hope the day never comes
where you have to read this.

551
00:50:33,761 --> 00:50:37,973
A woman came to see me
and said strange things about you.

552
00:50:39,349 --> 00:50:41,351
To be honest, it shook me.

553
00:50:54,782 --> 00:50:57,201
This is Seung-jae's handwriting.

554
00:50:59,328 --> 00:51:01,330
He left a clue about the culprit.

555
00:51:03,832 --> 00:51:04,833
[gasps]

556
00:51:14,843 --> 00:51:17,679
- Are you okay?
- [gasping]

557
00:51:19,348 --> 00:51:20,349
Seol-ah.

558
00:51:22,434 --> 00:51:24,770
[sobbing, gasping]

559
00:51:46,625 --> 00:51:47,626
INSURANCE APPLICATION FORM

560
00:51:48,836 --> 00:51:50,921
INSURANCE AGENT: KIM MI-SUK

561
00:51:52,756 --> 00:51:53,799
[door closes]

562
00:51:57,594 --> 00:51:59,721
This is your parents'
life insurance policy.

563
00:52:01,849 --> 00:52:03,350
Check the agent's name for me.

564
00:52:05,352 --> 00:52:06,769
I think it might be someone you know.

565
00:52:06,770 --> 00:52:08,188
INSURANCE AGENT: KIM MI-SUK

566
00:52:22,661 --> 00:52:24,997
These photos were found
at Paek Jun-beom's house.

567
00:52:25,747 --> 00:52:29,042
I skimmed through them back then,
but there were some with Kim Yun-ji.

568
00:52:33,380 --> 00:52:37,509
That means she was in Cheongun
the day before Seung-jae died.

569
00:52:38,510 --> 00:52:39,887
Until the next morning.

570
00:52:43,307 --> 00:52:46,018
And this one here
was taken by the river that day.

571
00:52:55,319 --> 00:52:58,322
So, Kim Yun-ji was a witness, right?

572
00:52:59,948 --> 00:53:02,451
And she knew who murdered Seung-jae.

573
00:53:03,535 --> 00:53:05,162
That's why she was killed.

574
00:53:07,122 --> 00:53:08,123
[sighs]

575
00:53:09,625 --> 00:53:11,834
You think this could serve as evidence?

576
00:53:11,835 --> 00:53:15,797
Well, it may not be enough,
but the culprit will show up soon,

577
00:53:16,882 --> 00:53:20,302
because I'm with Han Seol-ah
and I know their secret.

578
00:53:21,386 --> 00:53:23,554
- If I don't take that chance--
- Oh, no.

579
00:53:23,555 --> 00:53:25,723
I'm not going to be using you as bait.

580
00:53:25,724 --> 00:53:29,518
I'm the only one who can get close
without raising suspicion.

581
00:53:29,519 --> 00:53:31,520
- I'll do it.
- It's too risky.

582
00:53:31,521 --> 00:53:32,772
Even Chair Kim is dead.

583
00:53:32,773 --> 00:53:37,068
What's dangerous is always living
with anxiety and in constant fear.

584
00:53:37,069 --> 00:53:38,903
I don't want to live like that anymore.

585
00:53:38,904 --> 00:53:40,404
Then let's go together.

586
00:53:40,405 --> 00:53:41,990
Together we'll get caught.

587
00:53:45,160 --> 00:53:48,288
Woo-seok, isn't there something
you need to look into?

588
00:53:49,456 --> 00:53:51,457
Let me know the route you're taking,

589
00:53:51,458 --> 00:53:53,293
and I'll keep you in the loop
about mine too.

590
00:53:57,005 --> 00:53:58,298
Be careful.

591
00:54:02,552 --> 00:54:04,471
- [door closes]
- [engine starts]

592
00:54:08,475 --> 00:54:11,352
[Gong] You know,
I still suspect Do Eun-hyuk,

593
00:54:11,353 --> 00:54:12,603
but he has an alibi.

594
00:54:12,604 --> 00:54:16,565
The CCTV footage shows
that he was at his studio in Cheongun

595
00:54:16,566 --> 00:54:18,276
when Paek Jun-beom was killed.

596
00:54:18,902 --> 00:54:22,030
["Fear Inside" playing]

597
00:54:50,475 --> 00:54:53,311
CHEONGUN STUDIO

598
00:54:54,896 --> 00:54:57,065
RECOMMENDED ROUTE
16 MINUTES

599
00:54:58,608 --> 00:55:00,652
If I step on the gas the whole way...

600
00:55:51,745 --> 00:55:53,955
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

601
00:56:10,180 --> 00:56:12,432
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

602
00:56:38,583 --> 00:56:40,794
DO EUN-HYUK

603
00:56:59,563 --> 00:57:01,021
[Woo-seok] As long as the road is clear,

604
00:57:01,022 --> 00:57:03,691
it's possible to get
from Paek Jun-beom's villa

605
00:57:03,692 --> 00:57:06,069
to the studio in under 15 minutes.

606
00:57:59,539 --> 00:58:01,916
PHOTO EQUIPMENT PURCHASE
LIVING EXPENSES

607
00:58:01,917 --> 00:58:03,584
DO EUN-HYE PRIVATE TUTORING EXPENSES

608
00:58:03,585 --> 00:58:04,794
LIVING EXPENSES

609
00:58:06,922 --> 00:58:08,548
EQUIPMENT PURCHASE

610
00:58:27,067 --> 00:58:29,444
DARKROOM & LARGE TANK INSTALLATION
SOUNDPROOFING WORK

611
00:59:43,310 --> 00:59:44,561
[hammer cocks]

612
00:59:50,942 --> 00:59:52,276
[Woo-seok] I'm going to Cheongun.

613
00:59:52,277 --> 00:59:54,446
CHA WOO-SEOK

614
01:00:00,410 --> 01:00:01,578
[Eun-hyuk] Don't worry.

615
01:00:02,954 --> 01:00:05,332
It'll all work out the way you want.

616
01:00:31,566 --> 01:00:32,859
Do Eun-hyuk.

617
01:01:18,530 --> 01:01:20,323
[Woo-seok] If you fall in love
with Han Seol-ah,

618
01:01:21,491 --> 01:01:22,617
you will die.

619
01:01:23,993 --> 01:01:25,577
[people shouting, screaming]

620
01:01:25,578 --> 01:01:27,579
I gained nothing at all.

621
01:01:27,580 --> 01:01:28,705
No!

622
01:01:28,706 --> 01:01:30,542
[Seol-ah] I only lost.

623
01:01:31,126 --> 01:01:33,169
[Woo-seok] If the culprit
thinks I'm your boyfriend,

624
01:01:33,753 --> 01:01:35,296
I'll end up dead,

625
01:01:36,423 --> 01:01:38,090
or I'll find out who the killer is.

626
01:01:38,091 --> 01:01:40,050
What if you really end up dead?

627
01:01:40,051 --> 01:01:42,637
[Woo-seok] I said I don't care.
You can use me.

628
01:01:43,596 --> 01:01:45,598
- [Seol-ah] So until we catch the killer...
- [screams]

629
01:01:46,850 --> 01:01:48,517
...nothing is over yet.

630
01:01:48,518 --> 01:01:50,519
[Woo-seok] But the culprit
will show up soon,

631
01:01:50,520 --> 01:01:51,854
because I'm with Han Seol-ah...

632
01:01:51,855 --> 01:01:53,940
- [grunts]
- ...and I know their secret.
